subSubSection.paragraph:
Proposed common name: Red Sea flathead (
Figs. 6–7
)

Description. Dorsal fin spines I, VIII, rays 11 ; anal fin rays 12 ; P rays 19 ; pored LL scales 52 ( 50–53 ); anterior 3 scales bearing small spines ( 2–4 ); GR 1 + 5 = 6 ; branched caudal-fin rays 10 ; vertebrae 27 . Villiform teeth in bands on jaws, with small canines at symphysis, on palatines and in two separate patches on vomer. LL scale pores with two openings to the exterior (
Fig. 7
). Iris lappet with short branches. Orbital diameter 1.1–1.4 in snout length (
Fig. 11
); snout length 3.1 (2.8–3.2) in HL.
